Durban â€“ A 12-year-old boy has been shot dead on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast after allegedly being mistaken for a monkey.
Bongumusa Duma was killed in Braemar while picking guavas in a tree.
Police spokesman Lieutenant Thulani Zwane said the incident happened just before 9am on Sunday morning. 
An 87-year-old man was arrested on the scene. 
Scottburgh police spokesman Captain Vincent Pandarum told the South Coast Herald that the man said he had mistaken the boy in the tree for a monkey and shot him with a licensed shotgun.
Zwane said the man will appear at the Umzinto court on Tuesday.
